# Lesson candidate: a guard on the DETECTOR is not a guard on the SOURCE

**Surfaced:** 2026-06-27 conductor (G18 fire, commit cf3ef6a)

## Symptom
`Gamma_SwarmPremarket` + `Gamma_ContextGuard` flashed an OpenConsole window on every
fire and tripped `audit_scheduled_tasks.py` BARE_CMD_POWERSHELL (HEALTH RED) -- even
though `setup/fix-powershell-task-flash.ps1` had *already* converted them to the
windowless wscript chain weeks earlier, and `test_guard_cmd_popup_fix_ws6.py` was green.

## Root cause (two compounding mechanisms)
1. **A fixer's effect was silently undone by a later re-registration script that was
   never updated to the new pattern.** The 2026-06-26 TZ-systemic fix
   `register_tz_fixed_tasks.ps1` re-registered both tasks with BARE `powershell.exe`
   actions (its section #3 SpendSummary already used the correct wscript chain, but #1/#2
   did not). A re-run of the TZ fixer re-clobbered the flash fix. Same class as the
   TZ-install time-bomb, but for the *window-hiding* property instead of the *schedule*.
2. **The existing guard tested the DETECTOR, not the SOURCE.** `test_guard_cmd_popup_fix_ws6.py`
   only exercised the audit's `_is_bare_console_launcher` / `_is_hidden` helpers against
   synthetic strings -- it proved the audit *can* detect a bare action, never that no
   installer *emits* one. So an installer re-introducing a bare action stayed green; the
   regression only surfaced live, in the audit's HEALTH flag (and that audit was itself
   stuck RED for unrelated reasons -- see L189 -- so even the live signal was muted).

## Fix (shipped)
`backtest/tests/test_installer_no_bare_console_action.py` (4/4, bite-tested): a STATIC
scan of `setup/**/*.ps1` that fails if any installer constructs a task with a bare
`-Execute "powershell.exe"`/`"cmd.exe"`. Pins the 3 fixed installers clean + a shrinks-only
ratchet over 6 pre-existing latent offenders. Source fixes applied to all 3 clobberers.

## Principle (reusable -- candidate fold into C7, sibling to L189)
When a property is enforced by a fixer/converter script, GUARD THE ARTIFACT THE PRODUCER
WRITES, not the validator's detection logic. "The audit can detect X" + "no producer emits
not-X" are two different invariants; only the second prevents a later script from silently
undoing the fix. A green detector-unit-test next to a red live-audit is the tell.

## Related
L189 (audit the real artifact not a proxy; persistently-RED audit masks new breakage),
project_scheduled_task_tz (one fixer's output clobbered by another re-registration),
project_mcp_window_leak_fix (the bare-powershell OpenConsole flash class).
